    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Box Model Example</title>
    <style>
        .outer-box {
            width: 300px;
            height: 300px;
            background-color: #f28c28; /* Orange */
            border: 4px solid black;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .inner-box {
            width: 90%;
            height: 90%;
            background-color: yellow;
            border: 3px solid black;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .label {
            background-color: lightyellow;
            border: 2px solid black;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            width: fit-content;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h2 style="text-align:center;">Box Model Example (CSS)</h2>
<div class="outer-box">
    <div class="inner-box">
        <div class="label">M.Sc (Computer Sci)</div>
        <div class="label">Academic Year<br>2023–24</div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>

Slip 14
1.	Write a css3 script for the student registration form with appropriate message display also highlight compulsory fields in a different color.
Solution: <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Student Registration</title>
<style>
    body{
        font-family: Arial;
        padding: 20px;
    }
    .form-box{
        width: 350px;
        padding: 20px;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        border-radius: 8px;
    }
    input, select{
        width: 100%;
        padding: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        border: 1px solid #888;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }
    /* Highlight compulsory fields */
    input:required, select:required{
        border-color: red;
        background: #ffe6e6;
    }
    /* Message on focus */
    input:focus::after {
        content: "Please fill this field";
        color: green;
        font-size: 12px;
    }
    label{
        font-weight: bold;
    }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="form-box">
    <h3>Student Registration</h3>
    <form>
        <label>Name *</label>
        <input type="text" required>
        <label>Age *</label>
        <input type="number" required>
        <label>Email *</label>
        <input type="email" required>
        <label>Course</label>
        <select required>
            <option>Select Course</option>
            <option>BCA</option>
            <option>BSc IT</option>
            <option>MCA</option>
        </select>
        <input type="submit" value="Register">
    </form>
</div>
</body>
</html>



