Slip 16
1.	Create a web page to create 3D text. Apply all text effects like text shadow, text overflow, wordwrap etc.
Solution: <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
<title>3D Text & Text Effects</title>
<style>
  body{
    font-family: "Segoe UI", Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
    display:flex;
    gap:2rem;
    align-items:flex-start;
    justify-content:center;
    padding:3rem;
    background:#0f172a;
    color:#fff;
  }

  /* Container card */
  .card{
    width:380px;
    background:#0b1220;
    padding:18px;
    border-radius:10px;
    box-shadow:0 10px 30px rgba(2,6,23,.6);
  }

  /* 3D/extruded text (stacked shadows) */
  .three-d{
    font-size:56px;
    font-weight:900;
    line-height:1;
    letter-spacing:1px;
    display:inline-block;
    margin-bottom:12px;
    color:#fff;
    /* many shadows -> extrusion */
    text-shadow:
      1px 1px 0 #d1d5db,
      2px 2px 0 #cbd5e1,
      3px 3px 0 #b8c4d6,
      4px 4px 0 #98a8bd,
      5px 5px 0 #7b8aa0,
      6px 6px 8px rgba(2,6,23,.6);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg,#ffd54d 0%, #ff7a59 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    transform: translateZ(0); /* GPU layer for smoothness */
  }

  /* subtle glow */
  .glow{
    text-shadow:
      0 2px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.06),
      0 6px 20px rgba(255,122,89,.16);
  }

  /* Single-line truncation with ellipsis */
  .single-line{
    width:100%;
    white-space:nowrap;
    overflow:hidden;
    text-overflow:ellipsis;
    border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    padding:.5rem;
    margin-top:.75rem;
    font-size:14px;
    color:#d1d5db;
  }

  /* Multiline with wrapping and break long words */
  .multi-line{
    margin-top:.8rem;
    max-height:6.2rem;
    overflow:auto;
    line-height:1.4;
    padding:.5rem;
    border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    font-size:14px;
    color:#d1d5db;
    /* permit breaking of long words */
    word-wrap: break-word;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
    hyphens: auto;
  }
  /* demo: extremely long word to force a break */
  .longword{ font-weight:700; color:#ffd54d; }

  /* small interactions */
  .three-d:hover{ transform:translateY(-4px); transition:transform .18s ease; cursor:default; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="card" aria-label="3D text demo">
  <div class="three-d glow" role="heading" aria-level="1">3D TEXT</div>
  <div class="single-line" title="This shows text-overflow with ellipsis">
    This is an example of a very long single-line sentence that will be truncated with an ellipsis if it overflows the container.
  </div>
 <div class="multi-line" aria-live="polite">
    This paragraph demonstrates <strong>word-wrap</strong> and <strong>overflow-wrap</strong>. If a user pastes a verylongwordwithoutanyspacesitwillbreakbecause CSS rules allow it to wrap. Example: 
    <span class="longword">SupercalifragilisticexpialidociousSupercalifragilistic</span>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
Slip 17
1.	Create an html page named as “calendar.html” Use necessary input types and get following output.
Solution: <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Input Types Examples</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Input Types Examples</h2>
    <form>
        Date: <input type="date"><br><br>
        Datetime: <input type="datetime"><br><br>
        Datetime-local: <input type="datetime-local"><br><br>
        Month: <input type="month"><br><br>
        Time: <input type="time"><br><br>
        Week: <input type="week"><br><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
</body>
</html>

